# Makes an Arduino Library from the AVR2025 distribution

How to use (Win32)

1. Install https://github.com/logos-electromechanical/Zigduino and ensure it's fully set up.
2. Unpack this distribution where you put your Arduino libaries, e.g. C:\users\me\Documents\Arduino\libraries\AVR2025
3. Download Atmel's IEEE 802.15.4 MAC distribution from http://www.atmel.com/dyn/products/tools_card.asp?tool_id=4675 and unpack it somewhere
4. Download and install gawk http://gnuwin32.sourceforge.net/packages/gawk.htm
5. Edit fileprep.cmd...
6. ...Update the MAC_INSTALL variable to where you installed the MAC
7. ...Update the GAWK variable to the location of the gawk binary, typically "C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin\gawk.exe"
8. Open a command window, cd to the AVR2025 directory
9. Type "fileprep.cmd"
10. Exit Arduino
11. Start Arduino
12. Select File > Examples > AVR2025 > Star_NoBeacon
13. Verify
14. Upload
15. Smile!
